&lt;p&gt;BAND 6 TREATMENT PLANNING DOSIMETRIST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Guy’s and St Thomas’ NHS Trust (GSTT) has embarked upon a comprehensive cancer strategy that will shape the future of services for the next generation of cancer patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a research radiographer/dosimetrist with experience in radiotherapy contouring and treatment planning to join our team to support a Wellcome Trust Funded award. This work aims to develop advanced artificial intelligence approaches for the rapid contouring and planning of palliative radiotherapy, to enable safe, affordable and rapid delivery of radiotherapy treatment for acute oncological conditions related to locally advanced and widely disseminated cancers, within 10 minutes of receiving a CT scan. The particular focus of this automated treatment planning approach is for patients from low and middle income countries where only 10-40% of patients have access to radiotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The study at Guy’s Cancer Centre is in partnership with the MD Anderson Cancer Centre (USA) who are leading the study and Stellenbosch University Cape Town, South Africa.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Medical Physics at Guys &amp; St.Thomas’ provides a comprehensive range of scientific and technical services to the Trust and external organisations. We are looking for experienced candidates capable of undertaking a diverse range of work related to this project, particularly clinical data curation and annotation as well as supporting clinical teams. Previous involvement in radiotherapy research is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this post and would like an informal discussion then please contact Dr Ajay Aggarwal (Consultant Clinical Oncologist), email: ajay.aggarwal@gstt.nhs.uk or Tony Greener, Head of Radiotherapy Physics, Tel. 02071887188 ext. 57539, email: tony.greener@gstt.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
